Can Chagas disease be transmitted by acai juice sold in the USA?

--
Dee Hadorn
Cerulean Farm
Harrah, OK
USA
<bluemohair@gmail.com>

[ProMED-mail thanks Dee Hadorn for her important question. So far, infections have only been registered after drinking freshly pressed fruit juice. We do not know, but it seems highly unlikely that trypanosomes can survive prolonged storage at +4 deg C (39 deg F) and definitely not pasteurization.

It is not likely that transmission by fruit juice processed, canned, and shipped would be unnoticed and no such reports exist to our knowledge.

The conclusion is that the acai juice sold in the USA most probably are completely safe. - Mod.EP]
